<HEAD>`Free the Lunch, Hold the Mayo'</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hundreds of costumed revelers paraded
through the Financial District, celebrating ``St. Stupid's Day'' in
a parade sponsored by the ``First Church of the Last Laugh.''
   The revelers _ most wearing dunce caps, gorilla outfits, roller
skates, tap shoes or capes _ chanted ``free the lunch, hold the
mayo'' and other nonsensical phrases during the traditional April
Fools Day procession Friday.
   ``This parade is dedicated to the fools, bimbos, bozos and
ding-a-lings who know how to have a good time,'' said actor Ed
Holmes.
   Not everyone who saw the affair were entertained.
   ``I think this is pretty stupid,'' said Alex Nisenbaum, an
8-year-old from Loomis visiting the city. ``Grown-ups are really
weird.''
