<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police combed a neighborhood today for a
carload of gang members who fired on pedestrians as they drove by,
killing one and wounding 12 others, including a 4-year-old boy,
authorities said.
   The gunmen indiscriminately shot at people standing on a
sidewalk Friday night in a gang-ridden area of south Los Angeles,
said Deputy Police Chief William Rathburn.
   No motive was given for the shootings. ```It's a little too
early,'' said a policeman who declined to give his name. ``The
officers are still out there hustling up whatever they can find.''
   Extra officers were dispatched to help look for three men in a
brown Cadillac, Rathburn said.
   Thirteen people were hit by gunfire, said police Cmdr. William
Booth, but only 11 could be accounted for at hospitals. Authorities
said two of the wounded may have sought medical attention on their
own.
