Los Angeles County-USC Medical Center, said hospital spokeswoman
Adelaida de la Certa. None of the victims' names were immediately
available.
   The 4-year-old boy was in serious but stable condition with
wounds in the side, arm and legs, Ms. de la Certa said.
   A 29-year-old man with leg and hand wounds and a 20-year-old man
with a leg wound were in fair condition, she said.
   A man was in critical condition at the Hospital of the Good
Samaritan with gunshot wounds to the stomach and legs, said a
nursing supervisor who refused to be identified. Another man was
treated and released.
   Two men with leg wounds were in fair condition at Daniel Freeman
Memorial Hospital, said nursing supervisor Christie Ciraulo.
   A 29-year-old man was taken to California Medical Center with
minor injuries, but it was uncertain whether he would be admitted,
said a nursing supervisor who refused to give her name.
   A 16-year-old and another teen-age boy were treated at other
hospitals and released, officials said.
