<1ST_LINE>r a AM-JudgeFast     04-02 0242</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Judge Fast,0247</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Suspended Judge Plans To Fast For 40 Days</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MINNEAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A county judge said he has begun a 40-day
fast to demonstrate his credibility in the face of an attempt to
remove him from the bench for allegedly making sexual advances to a
male court reporter.
   Ramsey County District Judge Alberto Miera, who has denied the
allegation, said Friday his bisexuality and the fact that he is
Hispanic have been factors in the attempt to remove him.
   ``I feel obligated to do that to prevent this kind of abuse and
injustice from happening to other individuals who are socially
vulnerable, and to encourage people to recognize that they have to
stand up and fight even though there may be costs,'' said Miera,
who will take liquids throughout the fast and have one meal every
other day.
   The state Board on Judicial Standards in February recommended
Miera be removed for allegedly making sexual advances to his former
male court reporter and for other judicial misconduct. The judge
was convicted last year of battery for forcibly kissing the former
court reporter.
   The state Supreme Court temporarily suspended him March 9 to
consider the recommendation. Arguments are scheduled May 24.
   ``It's not me that's the issue anymore,'' Miera said. ``It's the
concept of justice, it's the concept of how we treat people, it's
the concept of whether we treat people differently because we're
fearful of what they represent,'' he said.
</TEXT>
