<1ST_LINE>r w AM-BRF--PostalRates     04-02 0078</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Postal Rates,70</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Postage Charges Increase</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mailing a letter costs more starting Sunday,
as new postage rates go into effect.
   It will cost 25 cents to mail first-class letters, up 3 cents.
   The second ounce of first-class mail also rises 3 cents, to 20
cents.
   But postal cards are up only a penny, to 15 cents.
   The rate increases cover most classes of mail, with larger hikes
for advertising and periodicals than for letters.
</TEXT>
