<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Eye Drops,0184</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>FBI, FDA Probing Eye Injury</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Aerial cq in 2nd graf</NOTE>
<DATELINE>SAN RAFAEL, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The FBI and the federal Food and Drug
Administration are probing an incident in which a nurse was blinded
by eye drops contaminated with a caustic chemical.
   ``Her left eye looks like it melted and her right eye looks like
it's covered with white glue,'' said Richard Critchlow, an attorney
for Aerial Van Zee Miller, 34, of Fairfax in Marin County.
   Although the Clear Eyes drops were found to contain a caustic
alkali solution, an FDA spokesman said Friday no recall will be
ordered unless it is found that the incident was not an isolated
case.
   Miller was taken to Marin General Hospital moments after she put
some of the solution into each eye Monday. Critchlow said 80
percent of Miller's left cornea and 60 percent of her right cornea
was destroyed, and doctors do not know if she'll ever recover her
sight.
   Cathy Babington, a spokeswoman for Abbott Laboratories, said
``there has never been a complaint before'' against Clear Eyes.
