<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BeachedFreighter     04-02 0109</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Beached Freighter,0110</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Freighter Runs Aground, Second In Two Days</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT LAUDERDALE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   For the second time in as many
days, a freighter has broken anchor in rough seas and run aground
just off the beach, the Coast Guard reported Saturday.
   The 128-foot Honduran freighter Brac Express with five crew
members became mired 30 yards offshore Saturday at about 2:30 a.m.
EST, said Coast Guard spokesman Luis Diaz. He said the Coast Guard
was not certain of the cargo.
   On Friday, a 506-foot empty petroleum barge bobbed about 20
yards from the beach most of the day before it was towed off early
in the evening.
</TEXT>
